t of access to space. The Falcon 9 rocket, for instance, is designed to return to Earth and be reused multiple times.\n\n2. **Commercial Spaceflight**: SpaceX has played a crucial role in the commercialization of space travel. It was the first private company to send a spacecraft (Dragon) to the International Space Station (ISS) in 2012, marking a significant milestone in private space exploration.\n\n3. **Crewed Missions**: The company developed the Crew Dragon spacecraft, which successfully transported astronauts to the ISS as part of NASA's Commercial Crew Program. This marked the first crewed launch from U.S. soil since the Space Shuttle program ended in 2011.\n\n4. **Starship Development**: SpaceX is currently developing the Starship spacecraft, which aims to enable missions to Mars and beyond. Starship is designed to be fully reusable and capable of carrying large numbers of passengers and cargo.\n\n5. **Satellite Internet**: Through its Starlink project, SpaceX is deploying a constellation of satellites to provide global high-speed internet coverage, which has implications for communication in remote areas and future space missions.\n\n### Achievements:\n- **First Privately Funded Liquid-Fueled Rocket**: In 2008, SpaceX's Falcon 1 became the first privately developed liquid-fueled rocket to reach orbit.\n- **First Private Company to Reach the ISS**: The Dragon spacecraft made history in 2012 by becoming the first commercial spacecraft to deliver cargo to the ISS.\n- **First Reusable Orbital Rocket**: The Falcon 9 rocket's first stage successfully landed back on Earth in 2015, demonstrating the feasibility of reusability in space travel.\n- **Crewed Spaceflight**: In May 2020, SpaceX's Crew Dragon successfully transported NASA astronauts to the ISS, marking a new era in commercial spaceflight.\n\nOverall, SpaceX has transformed the landscape of space exploration, making it more accessible and cost-effective while pushing the boundaries of what is possible in aerospace technology.", additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 494, 'prompt_tokens': 439, 'total_tokens': 933, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0, 'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': 0}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': 0, 'cached_tokens': 0}, 'input_tokens': 0, 'output_tokens': 0, 'input_tokens_details': None}, 'model_name': 'gpt-4o-mini', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_eb37e061ec', 'finish_reason': 'stop', 'logprobs': None}, id='run-0ed53208-1b7a-4afd-9efe-670280941bc6-0', usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 439, 'output_tokens': 494, 'total_tokens': 933, 'input_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'cache_read': 0}, 'output_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'reasoning': 0}})], 'is_last_step': False}
